ARDS LIBRARY UNIFICATION.     A TEXT PREPARED BY THE PUBLIC LIBRARIES SECTION OF THE ASSOCIATION DESBIBLIOTHECAIRES FRANCAIS (ABF) TO SUPPORT THE 1981 CONFERENCE MOTION ONLIBRARY UNIFICATION. A PRELIMINARY DISCUSSION BRIEFLY INTRODUCES THE ISSUESINVOLVED IN ESTABLISHING AN INTEGRATED NATIONAL NETWORK, IN THE FACE OF AGOVERNMENT POLICY OF DECENTRALISATION. THE ABF PROGRAMME FOR ACHIEVINGUNIFICATION IN SERVICE PROVISION, PERSONNEL ALLOCATION, AND PERSONNELTRAINING, IS THEN ELABORATED. IN EACH CASE DETAILS ARE GIVEN OF THE EXISTINGORGANISATION OF RESOURCES, THE ADVANTAGES OF UNIFICATION OUTLINED, AND THEMEANS OF IMPLEMENTING A POLICY OF INTEGRATION INDICATED